'''COGEN Europe''' is a European [[advocacy group]] based in [[Belgium]] that promotes the practice of [[cogeneration]] in energy production. The group acts as a liaison between its member companies and [[European Union]] energy organizations and committees.<ref>[http://www.cogeneurope.eu/about-cogen-europe_2.html COGEN Europe]</ref><ref>[http://www.code-project.eu/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/D6.1-Proposal-for-a-European-Cogeneration-Roadmap.pdf Growing cogeneration in Europe]</ref><ref>[http://www.chpa.co.uk/microchp-championed-by-cogen-europe-in-latest-position-statement_1520.html MicroCHP championed by COGEN Europe in latest position statement]</ref>
The managing director of COGEN Europe is also the coordinator of the [http://enefield.eu/ ene.field project].<ref>[http://www.fch-ju.eu/sites/default/files/documents/sga2012/Presentation%20Fiona%20Riddoch-%20Session%20II.pdf 5th stakeholders general assembly of the FCH JU]</ref>
